Description: Body sherd of Milesian pre-Fikellura pottery cup; white slip; interior: painted decoration consisting of bitch (only back, underbelly with swollen teets, rump, tail and part of hind leg remaining), to right; dot rosettes as filling ornament; exterior: overlapping rosette pattern.
Curator's comments: Rosettes are also found on Fikellura oinochoai, see British Museum 1888,0601.556.b and 1888,0601.556.c). Cook placed those sherds into his group of 'Miscellaneous Oinochoai', and dated them to circa 550BC.
